<link href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=2109&amp;p=10636#p10636"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Save Start menu pinned items ?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=2109&amp;p=10636#p10636"><![CDATA[
Yes definitely. Depending on your settings for &quot;Pinned Programs folder&quot;, pinned items are stored at C:\Users\&lt;your user name&gt;\AppData\Roaming\Microsoft\Windows\Start Menu or at C:\Users\&lt;your user name&gt;\AppData\Roaming\ClassicShell\Pinned. You can also back up all the shortcuts inside the two Start Menu folders: the first one mentioned earlier and the All Users Start Menu at C:\ProgramData\Microsoft\Windows\Start Menu.<br /><br />To save Classic Start Menu custom items which you may have added from the Customize Start Menu tab in settings, backup your settings to an XML file using the Backup button in settings.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=54">Gaurav</a> — Mon Feb 03, 2014 10:33 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
